The paper proposes a method for tuning analytic pipelines using Bayesian optimization, which is a common technique in machine learning and optimization. The paper also mentions experiments on benchmark datasets and a real-world application for healthcare predictive modeling, indicating a focus on practical applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
